'''社會無政府主義'''（'''Social anarchism'''或'''Socialist anarchism'''<ref name="Ostergaard p. 14">Ostergaard, Geoffrey. "Anarchism". ''The Blackwell Dictionary of Modern Social Thought''. Blackwell Publishing. p. 14.</ref>），也稱'''無政府社會主義'''（'''Anarcho-socialism'''或'''Anarchist socialism'''）<ref>Proudhon, Pierre-Joseph (1893). ''What is Property?'', p. 118</ref>、社群無政府主義（Communitarian anarchism）<ref>Morris, Christopher W. 1998. ''An Essay on the Modern State''. Cambridge University Press. p. 74</ref>（可與[[自由意志社會主義|自由意志社會主義]]<ref name="Ostergaard p. 14"/>、左派自由意志主義<ref>{{cite book|title=Social Anarchism Or Lifestyle Anarchism: An Unbridgeable Chasm|last=Bookchin|first=Murray|year=1995|publisher=AK Press}}</ref>、左派無政府主義<ref name=thagard>Thagard, Paul. 2002. ''Coherence in Thought and Action''. MIT Press. p. 153</ref>交替使用），是用來區分兩大類[[無政府主義|無政府主義]]的一種總稱，一類是[[集體主義|集體主義]]，另一類是[[個人無政府主義|個人無政府主義]]。個人主義型式的無政府主義強調個人自治和人類的理性，社會無政府主義者「將個人自由視為與社會平等在概念上的連結，強調社會公眾和互助」。<ref>Suissa, Judith(2001) "Anarchism, Utopias and Philosophy of Education" ''Journal of Philosophy of Education'' 35 (4), 627–646. doi:10.1111/1467-9752.00249 </ref> 不同於個人無政府主義著重在私有財產或財物的重要性，社會無政府主義反對私有財產，視為是社會不平等的來源。<ref>Ostergaard, Geoffrey. "Anarchism". A Dictionary of Marxist Thought. Blackwell Publishing, 1991. p. 21.</ref> 

社会无政府主义<ref>Baldelli, Giovanni (1971). [https://books.google.it/books?id=1pEO5ZAKW5AC&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6&dq=social+anarchism&source=bl&ots=BWb3H7Sut0&sig=ACfU3U02IG2wZGopeBFCA9Vxr_G9Tipv-w&hl=it&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiEstPMpavhAhUR3aQKHQQbB1oQ6AEwCXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=social%20anarchism&f=false ''Social Anarchism''] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=1pEO5ZAKW5AC&pg=PA6&lpg=PA6&dq=social+anarchism&source=bl&ots=BWb3H7Sut0&sig=ACfU3U02IG2wZGopeBFCA9Vxr_G9Tipv-w&hl=it&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiEstPMpavhAhUR3aQKHQQbB1oQ6AEwCXoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=social%20anarchism&f=false |date=20200412224136 }}. Aldine Atherton. Retrieved 31 March 2019.</ref><ref>[[Murray_Bookchin|Bookchin, Murray]] (1995). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/murray-bookchin-social-anarchism-or-lifestyle-anarchism-an-unbridgeable-chasm "Social Anarchism or Lifestyle Anarchism: An Unbridgeable Chasm"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/murray-bookchin-social-anarchism-or-lifestyle-anarchism-an-unbridgeable-chasm |date=20200413184437 }}. The Anarchist Library. Retrieved 31 March 2019.</ref><ref>McKay, Iain (18 June 2009). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/the-anarchist-faq-editorial-collective-an-anarchist-faq "An Anarchist FAQ"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/the-anarchist-faq-editorial-collective-an-anarchist-faq |date=20200413184404 }}. Stirling: AK Press.</ref><ref>Ehrlich, Howard J. (2013). [https://www.akpress.org/bestofsocialanarchism.html "The Best of Social Anarchism"] {{Wayback|url=https://www.akpress.org/bestofsocialanarchism.html |date=20190331042708 }}. See Sharp Press. Retrieved 31 March 2019. See also his ''[[Social_Anarchism_(journal)|Social Anarchism]]'' journal.</ref><ref>Owens, Connor (25 February 2016). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/connor-owens-why-social-anarchism "Why "Social" Anarchism?"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/connor-owens-why-social-anarchism |date=20200413184412 }}. The Anarchist Library. Retrieved 31 March 2019.</ref>作为[[无政府主义|无政府主义]]的一个分支，认为[[个人自由|个人自由]]与{{tsl|en|Mutual aid (organization theory)|互助 (组织理论)|互助}}相联系<ref name="Suissa, Judith 2001">Suissa, Judith (2001). "Anarchism, Utopias and Philosophy of Education". ''Journal of Philosophy of Education'' 35 (4). pp. 627–646. {{doi|10.1111/1467-9752.00249}}.</ref>。其理论强调[[社群|共同体]]和[[平等原則|平等原則]]是对[[自主權|自主權]]和[[公民自由|公民自由]]的补充，它试图通过在[[地方分权|地方分权]]的[[联邦主义|联邦制]]中保持[[言论自由|言论自由]]，思想自由和[[辅助性原则|辅助性原则]]来达到这种平衡。辅助性原则的最佳定义是“一个人不应该超出个人的范围，并向共同体承诺可以通过他们自己拥有的企业和工厂完成工作”并且“每一种社会机构都应该具有向社会成员提供帮助的性质，而不是统治或兼并他们”，最明显地表达这种特征的口号或许是“不要将自治的机构从人们手中夺走。”<ref name="Suissa, Judith 2001"/><ref>[[Pope_Pius_XI|Pius XI, Pope]] (15 May 1931). [https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/pius_xi/encyclicals/documents/hf_p-xi_enc_19310515_quadragesimo-anno_en.html ''Quadragesimo anno''] {{Wayback|url=https://www.vatican.va/holy_father/pius_xi/encyclicals/documents/hf_p-xi_enc_19310515_quadragesimo-anno_en.html |date=20160423101126 }}. §79.</ref>

社会无政府主义一直是无政府主义的主要流派。从术语上讲，强调[[社群主义|社群主义]]和[[合作社|合作社]]主义的社会无政府主义与[[个人无政府主义|个人无政府主义]]形成鲜明对比，同时与后者一样作为无政府主义，反对与[[集体思维|集体思维]]和[[从众行为|从众行为]]相关的[[威权|威权]][[共产主义|共产主义]]，这有利于[[个人|个人]]与[[社会|社会]]之间的和谐。同时社会无政府主义通过[[人民自決|人民自決]]，[[工人自治|工人自治]]，{{tsl|en|Anarchism and education|安那其主义与教育|教育}}，[[賦權|赋权]]并基于反权威的检查和警惕来抵制权威。尽管“检查”这一概念可能显得与无政府主义原则相违背，但实际上无政府主义的检查所指向的是个体对个人自由的捍卫和非强制：[[DIY|DIY]]的思想方法与社会领域的教育相结合<ref name="Dolgoff">[http://www.spunk.org/library/intro/sp001634.html "Misconceptions of Anarchism"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.spunk.org/library/intro/sp001634.html |date=20200413184340 }}. Spunk Library. In Dolgoff, Sam (1986). ''Fragments: A Memoir''. Refract Publications.</ref>。最重要的是，社会无政府主义还主张将现在和未来的私有[[生产资料|生产资料]]转换成[[公有制|公有制]]<ref name="Ostergaard">Ostergaard, Geoffrey (1991). "Anarchism". ''A Dictionary of Marxist Thought''. Blackwell Publishing. p. 21.</ref><ref name="Peacock">Peacock, Adrian (1999). ''Two Hundred Pharaohs, Five Billion Slaves''. London: Ellipsis.</ref><ref name="Goodwin">Goodwin, Barbara (2007). ''Using Political Ideas''. John Wiley & Sons.</ref>，它认为这么做可以通过更轻松地使用[[生产资料|生产资料]]来保持对[[動產|个人财产]]的尊重并通过共享公共资源来保护个人权利<ref name="Berkman">[[Alexander_Berkman|Berkman, Alexander]] (1929). [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Alexander_Berkman__What_Is_Communist_Anarchism_.html ''What Is Communist Anarchism?''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Alexander_Berkman__What_Is_Communist_Anarchism_.html |date=20120523195452 }}. "The revolution abolishes private ownership of the means of production and distribution, and with it goes capitalistic business. Personal possession remains only in the things you use. Thus, your watch is your own, but the watch factory belongs to the people".</ref>。

{{fact|社会无政府主义被认为是一个笼统的术语，因为它通常指代着诸如[[无政府共产主义|无政府共产主义]]、[[集体无政府主义|集体无政府主义]]以及{{tsl|en|Mutualism (economic theory)|互助主义|互助主义}}等概念，有时也可以包括由非国家控制的{{tsl|en|guild socialist|基爾特社會主義|基爾特社會主義}}联盟，基于企业内双重权力的[[产业民主|产业民主]]和{{tsl|en|economic democracy|经济民主|经济民主}}，甚至是主张由[[工人委员会|工人委员会]]联盟，[[工人委员会|工人委员会]]取代[[国家|国家]]并保留大部分基本权利的派系。此外，它还包括[[无政府工团主义|无政府工团主义]]的[[工会|工会]]理论，{{tsl|en|Platformism||Platformism}}和{{tsl|en|Especifismo||specifism}}的社会斗争策略以及[[社会生态学|社会生态学]]。作为一个术语，随着社会无政府主义的语义与发生重叠，在19世纪末与个人无政府主义相区别开后，以[[无政府共产主义|无政府共产主义]]取代“集体无政府主义”成为主要趋势}}。

社会无政府主义属于[[自由意志主义|自由意志主义]]<ref>"Anarchism". In Gaus, Gerald F.; D'Agostino, Fred, eds. (2012), more specifically, [[libertarian_socialism|libertarian socialism]]. ''The Routledge Companion to Social and Political Philosophy''. p. 227. "In its oldest sense, it is a synonym either for anarchism in general or social anarchism in particular".</ref>，[[自由意志社会主义|自由意志社会主义]]<ref name="Ostergaard p. 14" />，[[左翼自由主义|左翼自由主义]]<ref name="Bookchin 1995"/><ref name="Routledge p. 227"/>。它在十九世纪末兴起并与个人无政府主义相区别<ref>[http://anarchism.pageabode.com/afaq/secG2.html "An Anarchist FAQ"] {{Wayback|url=http://anarchism.pageabode.com/afaq/secG2.html |date=20130701112844 }}. "No, far from it.  So few anarchists found the individualist solution to the social question or the attempts of some of them to excommunicate social anarchism from the movement convincing".</ref>。

社会无政府主义被描述为无政府主义的集体主义或共产主义流派，并代表了与社会主义相适应的无政府主义形式，这令其与以个人无政府主义为代表的自由社会主义派形成鲜明对比。<ref>Boyd, Tony; Harrison, Kevin, eds. (2003). "Marxism and Anarchism". ''Understanding Political Ideas and Movements''. Manchester University Press. p. 251. {{ISBN|9780719061516}}.</ref><ref>{{cite book|editor-last=McKay|editor-first=Iain|year=2012|chapter=Section G – Is Individualist Anarchism Capitalistic?|title=An Anarchist FAQ|volume=II|location=Stirling|publisher=AK Press|isbn=9781849351225}}</ref><ref name="Franks 2013">{{cite journal|last=Franks|first=Benjamin|date=August 2013|editor-last1=Freeden|editor-first1=Michael|editor-last2=Stears|editor-first2=Marc|title=Anarchism|journal=The Oxford Handbook of Political Ideologies|publisher=Oxford University Press|pages=385–404|doi=10.1093/oxfordhb/9780199585977.013.0001}}</ref><ref>Carson, Kevin (2017). "Anarchism and Markets". In Jun, Nathan J. (2017). ''Brill's Companion to Anarchism and Philosophy''. BRILL. p. 81. {{ISBN|9789004356894}}.</ref>但是，一些集体或无政府共产主义者在激进的个人主义理论上建立了他们的理论<ref>[[Max_Baginski|Baginki, Max]] (May 1907). [http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/goldman/ME/mev2n3.html#142 "Stirner: The Ego and His Own"] {{Wayback|url=http://dwardmac.pitzer.edu/anarchist_archives/goldman/ME/mev2n3.html#142 |date=20170907103320 }}. ''[[Mother_Earth_(magazine)|Mother Earth]]'' (2: 3). "Modern Communists are more individualistic than Stirner. To them, not merely religion, morality, family and State are spooks, but property also is no more than a spook, in whose name the individual is enslaved — and how enslaved! [...] Communism thus creates a basis for the liberty and Eigenheit of the individual. I am a Communist because I am an Individualist. Fully as heartily the Communists concur with Stirner when he puts the word take in place of demand — that leads to the dissolution of property, to expropriation. Individualism and Communism go hand in hand."; [[Renzo_Novatore|Novatore, Renzo]] (1924). [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Renzo_Novatore__Toward_the_Creative_Nothing.html "Towards the Creative Nothing"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Renzo_Novatore__Toward_the_Creative_Nothing.html |date=20101128162745 }}; Gray, Christopher (1974). ''Leaving the Twentieth Century''. p. 88; [[Bob_Black|Black, Bob]] (2010). [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Bob_Black__Nightmares_of_Reason.html#toc22 "Nightmares of Reason"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Bob_Black__Nightmares_of_Reason.html#toc22 |date=20101027102331 }}. "[C]ommunism is the final fulfillment of individualism. [...] The apparent contradiction between individualism and communism rests on a misunderstanding of both. [...] Subjectivity is also objective: the individual really is subjective. It is nonsense to speak of "emphatically prioritizing the social over the individual," [...]. You may as well speak of prioritizing the chicken over the egg. Anarchy is a "method of individualization." It aims to combine the greatest individual development with the greatest communal unity".</ref>，将集体主义或共产主义视为实现个人自由的最佳社会制度。<ref name="Communism and Anarchy">[[Peter_Kropotkin|Kropotkin, Peter]] (1901). [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Petr_Kropotkin__Communism_and_Anarchy.html "Communism and Anarchy"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/60XT5iyby?url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Petr_Kropotkin__Communism_and_Anarchy.html |date=20110729121453 |dateformat=iso }}. "Communism is the one which guarantees the greatest amount of individual liberty — provided that the idea that begets the community be Liberty, Anarchy [...]. Communism guarantees economic freedom better than any other form of association, because it can guarantee wellbeing, even luxury, in return for a few hours of work instead of a day's work."; [[Dielo_Truda|Truda, Dielo]] (1926). [http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Dielo_Truda__Workers__Cause___Organisational_Platform_of_the_Libertarian_Communists.html "Organisational Platform of the Libertarian Communists"] {{WebCite|url=https://www.webcitation.org/60XT5tf40?url=http://www.theanarchistlibrary.org/HTML/Dielo_Truda__Workers__Cause___Organisational_Platform_of_the_Libertarian_Communists.html |date=20110729121456 |dateformat=iso }}. "This other society will be libertarian communism, in which social solidarity and free individuality find their full expression, and in which these two ideas develop in perfect harmony."; [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/various-authors-willful-disobedience-volume-2-number-12#toc18 "My Perspectives"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/various-authors-willful-disobedience-volume-2-number-12#toc18 |date=20200415141921 }}. ''Willful Disobedience'' (2: 12). "I see the dichotomies made between individualism and communism, individual revolt and class struggle, the struggle against human exploitation and the exploitation of nature as false dichotomies and feel that those who accept them are impoverishing their own critique and struggle."; [[L._Susan_Brown|Brown, L. Susan]] (2002). ''[[The_Politics_of_Individualism|The Politics of Individualism]]''. Black Rose Books; [[L._Susan_Brown|Brown, L. Susan]] (2 February 2011). [https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/l-susan-brown-does-work-really-work "Does Work Really Work?"] {{Wayback|url=https://theanarchistlibrary.org/library/l-susan-brown-does-work-really-work |date=20120613181303 }}.</ref> 个人主义-社会主义之间的区分也受到质疑，因为个人无政府主义在很大程度上是社会主义的，并且相互影响。<ref name="Franks 2013"/><ref>{{cite book|editor-last=McKay|editor-first=Iain|year=2012|title=An Anarchist FAQ|volume=II|location=Stirling|publisher=AK Press|isbn=9781849351225}}</ref>

在美國，「社會無政府主義」是指出版《社會無政府主義》這本刊物的圈子，之後由[[默里·布克钦|默里·布克钦]]所宣揚。布克金將社會無政府主義結合「[[左派|左派]]」，他在當中提到了「人類團結的優秀傳統與人性潛力的信念」、[[國際主義|國際主義]]和[[邦聯制|邦聯主義]]、[[民主|民主]]精神、[[反軍國主義|反軍國主義]]和理性的[[世俗主義|世俗主義]]。然而，宗教無政府主義和宗教左派則反對左派與「理性世俗主義」的合作，並發起了多次左翼宗教運動，如[[解放神學|解放神學]]和[[民權運動|民權運動]]。社會無政府主義致力於「自由結交的人們在自由社區內居住並合作」。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://flag.blackened.net/liberty/miscon.html |title=http://flag.blackened.net/liberty/miscon.html |accessdate=2009-06-20 |archive-date=1998-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/19980206141952/http://flag.blackened.net/liberty/miscon.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>
